Would it be terrible to think such a thing, and would this not destroy our faith in those of whom pull on the proverbial puppet strings. An ancient king of wisdom once pinned inspired words for Ecclesiastes, "man has dominated man to his harm" and another quote by an inspired Jeremiah stated, " It does not belong to man who is walking even to direct his step" or as the prophetic Israelite, Moses once wrote "Consequently, Jehovah(God) saw that man’s wickedness was great on the earth and that every inclination of the thoughts of his heart was only bad all the time"

For those who use God's word as a solemn resource, are probably familiar with the book written by John, pinned for our time, speaking of this revelation, "And I saw, and look! a pale horse, and the one seated on it had the name Death. And the Grave was closely following him"-"and with deadly plague". This scripture clearly identifies our day being characterized by great plagues. And he will wipe out every tear from their eyes, and death will be no more, neither will mourning nor outcry nor pain be anymore. The former things have passed away. And the One seated on the throne said: “Look! I am making all things new.
So the prophetic words of the Holy Scriptures doesn't just highlight the issues of humanity, but it also brings attention to the remedy of those issues, or for lack of better word the vaccine, that being, Jehovah God's Kingdom. So to all that struggle with the unknown in regard to our future, be confident that better times are to come, this pale horse will soon be stoped and it's rider will be final kicked off, and done away with.
